body: I was halfway through it when I realized I already read this before. As good as it is I really don't have the time to read reloaded stories. Please tag reloads so we don't have to waste time.

It's Raw and it's true and it's honest and it's liberating. A hauntingly beautiful memoir, a collection of memories and a personal story that you can relate to, not because you have been through the exact same things, but because we all have our demons and it is a really felicitous and happy coincidence when a writer manages to speak about all the matters that hurt and cut open.
Inseki. The watered down incest. Hypnosis mind control. An overused trope. The art is good though.
Sadly majority of his work is repetitive trash... there's like 1 work that actually good in term of story wise...
